CANADA DAYBOOK: Encana Reports Earnings, Election Campaigning

-- B y   P a u l   B a d e r t s c h e r
-- 
2011-04-20T05:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/canada-daybook-encana-reports-earnings-election-campaigning.html
Natural gas producer Encana reports
quarterly earnings, while  Canada ’s political leaders sharpen
their pitches ahead of the May 2 election.  WHAT TO WATCH: *Conservative Prime Minister Stephen Harper will
campaign in Quebec and  New Brunswick  for the May 2 federal
election, while Liberal Leader Michael Ignatieff will be in New
Brunswick and Nova Scotia. The Conservatives continue to lead in
public-opinion polls, although it remains unclear whether Harper
will be able to win a majority of seats in the House of Commons.  ECONOMY: * No major economic data is scheduled. Investors will
focus on tomorrow’s retail sales report for February, with
economists forecasting a 0.5% increase based on the median of 25
estimates in a Bloomberg survey.  EVENTS: *  Encana Corp. (ECA) , Canada’s largest natural gas producer,
reports quarterly earnings and holds its annual shareholder
meeting in Calgary. The company will likely post a profit in the
quarter from a loss a year earlier, according to analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg. 5 a.m. ET. *  Fairfax Financial Holdings
Ltd. (FFH)  hosts its annual  meeting  of shareholders at 9:30 a.m. in
Toronto. * The Bank of Canada will  auction  C$3.5 billion of a
new issue of 5-year bonds. Results will be posted by 12:05 p.m.  MARKETS:
*The S&P/TSX index rose 0.3 percent from a one-month low to
13,736.83.
*Yields on two-year Government of Canada bonds rose 8 basis
points to 1.77 percent at 4 p.m. in Toronto.
*The Canadian dollar rose to 95.63 cents per  U.S. dollar 
yesterday. One Canadian dollar bought $1.0457.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scanlan at   dscanlan@bloomberg.net . 